div#insurance-info-step
  // ─── Shared guide wrapper ───
  div.buckets-guide-container
    // ───────── Title & intro ─────────
    h2 🛡️ Get Your Insurance Spreadsheet Ready
    p
      | Before importing your <strong>Insurance</strong> data, make sure your
      | spreadsheet includes the following columns&nbsp;(✅&nbsp;required /
      | ⚙️&nbsp;optional):

    // ───────── Checklist ─────────
    ol.guide-steps
      li
        span.step-icon 1️⃣
        span.step-text
          strong Client ID (⚙️)
          |  – ties each policy to the correct client record.
      li
        span.step-icon 2️⃣
        span.step-text
          strong Policy Number (✅)
          |  – unique policy identifier; required to match/update records.
      li
        span.step-icon 3️⃣
        span.step-text
          strong Cash Value (⚙️)
          |  – current cash value.
      li
        span.step-icon 4️⃣
        span.step-text
          strong Carrier Name (⚙️)
          |  – e.g. Mutual of Omaha, Prudential.
      li
        span.step-icon 5️⃣
        span.step-text
          strong Policy Type (⚙️)
          |  – e.g. Whole Life, Term Life.
      li
        span.step-icon 6️⃣
        span.step-text
          strong Policy Sub Type (⚙️)
          |  – optional subtype or rider category.
      li
        span.step-icon 7️⃣
        span.step-text
          strong Effective Date (⚙️)
          |  – YYYY‑MM‑DD or MM/DD/YYYY.
      li
        span.step-icon 8️⃣
        span.step-text
          strong Expiration Date (⚙️)
          |  – YYYY‑MM‑DD or MM/DD/YYYY.

    // ───────── Tips ─────────
    p.mt-3
      | • Keep <em>Policy Number</em> unique but stable to avoid duplicates.  
      br
      | • If you have cash value data, include it for better reporting.  
      br
      | • Optional fields can be left blank; dates should be parseable.  
      br
      | • Start with our template to save time.

    // ───────── Download + Learn‑More ─────────
    a.import-action-item.d-block.mt-2(
      href='/downloads/insurance-import-template.xlsx'
      download
    )
      i.fas.fa-file-download.me-1
      | Download the Insurance Import template
    a.import-action-item.learn-more-btn.d-block.mt-2(
      href='#'
      data-video-id='76979872'
      data-bs-toggle='modal'
      data-bs-target='#learnMoreVideoModal'
    )
      i.fas.fa-play-circle.me-1
      | Watch an instructional video (2 min)

    // ───────── Example header row ─────────
    .example-header.mt-4
      h4 🧪 Example Header Row:
      code Client ID | Policy Number | Carrier Name | Policy Type | Policy Sub Type | Cash Value | Effective Date | Expiration Date
